I want to create a CRUD for some database entities.
the tables already exist

This is the structure I need 

-Every table must have a model defined in App\Models
-The templates must be plain blade templates, the form elements should preferably be written in plain html rather tha using laravel built-in functions to generate them, for the rest, standard laravel behaviour is expected, errors can be shown with flash session messages, I'm ok with that. I'm not gonna ask for front end validation except for the html native input attributes
-Every entity must have a Controller with one method for every route, these controllers must be placed in app\Http\Controllers\Admin
-The controllers must not access the models directly but through repository classes, the controllers only take care of receiving the requests inputs, calling the repositories, and returning the corresponding response
-Every entity has a repository, repositories can be all in the same directory such as app/Repositories
-Repositories must be loaded through dependency injection into the Controller methods
-All the routes related to the CRUD must be protected under spatie roles system so that only users with the role 'admin' can access them. this applies to post endpoints but also to the ones that show the crud pages (list, forms)
-If you think any other permission check layer is needed feel free to add it based on what I already said
-I will need a layout for all the CRUD teplates with a menu with links to all the entity list pages
-I don't need you to create any user with permissions, I will manage that my self

