-For all the entities with a place_id field, the input in edit/create forms must be a select for the records of the Place model
-For all the entities with a state_id field, the input in edit/create forms must be a select for the records of the State model
-For all the entities with a responsible_id field, the input in edit/create forms must be a select for the records of the Person model
-For all the entities with a person_id field, the input in edit/create forms must be a select for the records of the Person model
-For all the entities with a reservation_id field, the input in edit/create forms must be a select for the records of the Reservation model
-For all the entities with a price_item_id field, the input in edit/create forms must be a select for the records of the PriceItem model
-Controllers that load data of related entitities for the forms should also use the Repositories, for example if a list of places is needed for the activity table the places repository should be used from the controller

